The Telegraph - Calcutta : International
 Wednesday, March 24, 2004 				 Spain offers concessions to suspects
																								Madrid, March 23 (AFP): The two Indian nationals held in connection with the March 11 bombings in Madrid can receive lawyers and visitors, Spanish judicial sources said today.																								Vinay Kohly and Suresh Kumar were arrested two days after the bombings along with three Moroccans on suspicion of collaborating with a terrorist organisation and had since been held incommunicado in accordance with Spanish anti-terrorist laws.																								Reports last week said Kohly and Kumar were related by marriage and had lived in Madrid for 12 years. They were accused of cooperating with a terrorist group, sources said. The attacks were the worst in Spains history and which killed 190 people according to the latest tally of identified bodies released today. 
